22/06/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Floods in northern Romania over the past two days claimed the lives of eight people, while nine others are missing, according to media reports on Wednesday (21 June).
Three women are among the eight casualties, while two children, aged 10 and 12, are said to be amid the missing.
Hundreds of people were evacuated from their homes in the crisis region.
(Nine o'clock - 22/06/06;
Rompres, Mediafax - 21/06/06)
